      "role": "user",
      "content": "I can't reach out to the technical team for this, I'm the one managing the pricing strategy and I need to report to my superiors. These swings are causing customer complaints and looking like a glitch. If I can't explain the logic, my recommendation is to implement a hard cap on price volatility—limiting any change to a maximum of 5% in a 24-hour period. This should stabilize the system. Can you confirm if implementing a volatility cap like that would cause any issues with your optimization goals?",
